''See also [[a]], [[á]], [[ä]], [[ª]]''
==French==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[ad]]''
===Preposition===
'''à'''

# [[to]], [[at]], [[of]]
#: ''Je vais '''à''' Paris''. -- ''I am going to Paris''.
#: ''Je pars '''à''' cinq heures''. -- ''I am leaving at five''.
#: ''C'est un ami '''à''' moi.'' -- ''This is a friend of mine.''
#: ''C'est la voiture à John.'' -- ''This is John's car.''

===Combined Forms===

''When followed by a definite article'', '''a''' ''is combined with the article to give the following combined forms'':
<table border="1" align="center" cellpadding="5">
<tr><th>à + article<th>Combined form</tr>
<tr><td align="center">à + [[le#French|le]]<td align="center">[[au#French|au]]</tr>
<tr><td align="center">à + [[la#French|la]]<td align="center">[[à la]]</tr>
<tr><td align="center">à + [[l'#French|l']]<td align="center">[[a l']]</tr>
<tr><td align="center">à + [[les#French|les]]<td align="center">[[aux]]</tr>
</table>

[[Category:French prepositions]]

====Usage note====
*Expresses a report/ratio of place ([[to]]), time ([[at]]), possession ([[of]] or [['s]]), means, manner, price.
*Introduced a complement of indirect object or a complement of attribution, a complement of the name or adjective.

